ZH: 我脑子有点晕。
EN: My head is a little dizzy.

ZH: 他的脑子里装着很多知识。
EN: His brain is filled with a lot of knowledge.

ZH: 她的脑子里全是乱七八糟的念头。
EN: Her mind is filled with all sorts of thoughts.

ZH: 快把脑子里的疑问问出来。
EN: Ask the questions in your mind.

ZH: 我的脑子有点不够用了。
EN: My brain is a bit overloaded.

ZH: 他脑子里的想法总是让人大吃一惊。
EN: The thoughts in his mind always surprise people.

ZH: 挤满人的火车，每个人都拥有自己的脑海。
EN: In the crowded train, everyone has their own thoughts.

ZH: 他的脑子转得特别快。
EN: His brain works very fast.

ZH: 我把这个问题放在脑子里好几天了。
EN: I've been thinking about this problem for days.

ZH: 她的脑子里好像有个小人在捣鼓。
EN: There seems to be a little person tinkering in her mind.

ZH: 睡觉前不要操劳脑子。
EN: Don't stress your brain before bedtime.

ZH: 我们需要用脑子来解决这个谜题。
EN: We need to use our brains to solve this puzzle.

ZH: 学习新东西可以锻炼脑子。
EN: Learning new things can exercise the brain.

ZH: 他的脑子里装着各种各样的计划。
EN: His brain is filled with all kinds of plans.

ZH: 给脑子充电，要多读书。
EN: Charge up your brain, read more books.

ZH: 运动有助于保持脑子清晰。
EN: Exercise helps keep the brain clear.

ZH: 我的脑子里全是你的影子。
EN: Your shadow fills my mind.

ZH: 保持积极的心态可以让脑子更有活力。
EN: Keeping a positive attitude can make the brain more energetic.

ZH: 放松一下，别让脑子绞尽脑汁。
EN: Relax and don't rack your brain.

ZH: 我脑子一片空白，完全想不到解决办法。
EN: My mind is blank, I can't think of a solution at all.
